collections.name: The Adventures of Jesus Christ, 1 A.D - 2026 A.D.
collections.description:
I was influenced by a series of pulp novels, called casca, which was based on the premise that the Centurion who lanced Jesus was cursed to live through eternity as a warrior.
My mind started thinking, what if the role was reversed? what if jesus had lived from A.D.1 to today, what might he have done as a "normal"guy?
Hence my small collection of NFTs, The Adventures of Jesus.

Unlike most people, I dont have an online presence, no twitface, etc, so, if you have found me here on Opensea, Welcome :-)

collections.name: Runway Models - Futuristic Elements in Vibrant Modern Art
collections.description: This art piece merges high fashion with futuristic elements in a meticulously detailed and vibrant composition. The combination of runway models, cutting-edge fashion, and a whimsical character set against a modern industrial backdrop creates a visually striking narrative. The use of advanced photography and rendering techniques results in a highly realistic and polished image, blurring the lines between reality and digital artistry.

collections.name: Family Album by Ivona Tau
collections.description: Exploring family albums through the lens of memory loss, this project is derived from my personal photography archive spanning the 1960s and 1980s. Later in life, my mother experienced dementia, and her ensuing memory loss forms the heart of this work—my interpretation of how she perceived reality, often reliving her childhood. In this narrative, generations blend as her children’s memories intertwine with her own, allowing past and present to collapse into one.

collections.name: MUNUS
collections.description:
Robert Sonderberg creates works that evoke both clarity and depth.
In his latest collection, MUNUS, he explores the vital role of functionality in our everyday existence, blending artistic abstraction with practical purpose. Through clean lines and geometric compositions, he invites viewers to reflect on how simplicity and utility can shape our surroundings and our experiences. His art serves as a visual manifesto on the relevance of functional design, not only in the world of art but in life itself.

Robert Sonderberg's work continues to push the boundaries of modern art, making it a vital conversation piece for those who appreciate the power of simplicity and purpose in both form and function.
